pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=993.topic&index=91>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_sad.gif" align=absmiddle>  compassion and decency</span><hr size=1> If I thought that were the case, I'd agree with you.  But as I understand it, player of Sydia used to be player of Tori, who was a cleric on this server long before their guild was formed, even belonged to a role-playing guild which she left.  There are members of the guild who used to be in a variety of RP guilds on this server.   Jaxy was a member of the Intrepidity guild that merged with AS, though she subsequently left it.<br>
<br>
Discussions I had with members of AS in their first days on this server indicated that they know exactly what server they're on, that a core of them came here from another server to exploit low server population and the non no-drop items, and they have enough folks who were here long enough to understand the rest of this server and its population.<br>
<br>
I'm not flaming at you, I just question whether they even have a basic desire to work with or get along with anyone that they don't need something from, particularly anyone who isn't as strong as themselves as a guild.<br>
<br>
Controversy regarding ASs has reared its ugly head within the past 48 hours, over an issue which I'm still gathering data about.  Next time has already happened.<br>
<br>
I've personally had my own direct experiences with camp encroaching, general rudeness from a variety of ASs' members, training, not respecting areas they're passing through, . . . a whole list, from my personal experience, nevermind the stories from people I know and trust.<br>
<br>
I don't intend to fight fire with fire, I don't intend to become like them in order to cope with them, I don't want to be dragged down to their level of behavior in order to be successful on this server.  On the other hand, I don't intend to help them, ask help from them, and I won't buy/sell/trade with them (actually effective for a couple of weeks now).<br>
<br>
I've tried talking to a few of them a couple of times, trying to find the right words or concepts to express my opinion on the golden rule, but it's been like talking to a wall.  The leadership doesn't listen or seem to care, and the general members say that it's guild politics and policies and go talk to the leadership if there's a problem.  At some point, people have to take responsibility for their actions and the actions of the group which they're a part of.<br>
<br>
You have a point about people behaving like what you expect them to, and compassion is always one of the noblest of virtues.  But what do you do, when you keep trying to express positive attitudes and putting energy into something and folks don't respond, or continue to respond negatively?  How much investment in my time, your time, everyone's time, do we need to put forth in hopes that one day it will let up?   There is tolerance and compassion yes, but there comes a time when you have to say &quot;bad behavior won't be tolerated&quot;.<br>
<br>
Enough for now.<br>
<br>
